(Public Tender: City of Brookhaven Smart Mobility Data Platform) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Document Type: Requirement Specification / Tender) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. PROGRAM INTENT) Tj
T* (-----------------) Tj
T* (The City of Brookhaven seeks a unified data platform to aggregate public transit, traffic flow,) Tj
T* (parking occupancy, and EV charging utilization data.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The platform must support real-time dashboards for city operators and public transparency portals) Tj
T* (for residents.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (This procurement is funded by a federal smart city grant with strict audit and reporting) Tj
T* (obligations.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (2. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS) Tj
T* (--------------------------) Tj
T* (The solution shall ingest data from at least 27 source systems including GTFS feeds, IoT traffic) Tj
T* (sensors, and parking meter APIs.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The system must provide role-specific dashboards for transportation command center, planning) Tj
T* (office, and finance office.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The bidder must include configurable KPI calculations for congestion, route adherence, and parking) Tj
T* (turnover.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The platform must expose open data APIs for approved public datasets.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The system shall retain at least 7 years of historical data for compliance and trend analysis.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (3. SECURITY AND COMPLIANCE REQUIREMENTS) Tj
T* (---------------------------------------) Tj
T* (All personally identifiable information must be tokenized or anonymized before storage in) Tj
T* (analytical layers.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The vendor shall document CJIS-aligned controls because some integrations include law-enforcement) Tj
T* (adjacent feeds.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The solution must maintain audit logs for data access, admin actions, and schema changes.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Multi-factor authentication and least-privilege RBAC are mandatory.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (4. PROJECT DELIVERABLES) Tj
